The paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for automated brain tissue segmentation from MRI images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed approach uses a Fully Convolutional Neural Network (FCN), which is a popular deep learning architecture used for image segmentation tasks. This makes it likely to also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of skip connections, which are commonly used in neural networks for better feature extraction and identification. This makes it likely to also fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with medical image analysis, which is a sub-field of multimedia (cs.MM), making it a possible sub-category as well.
